%N A398008 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} d(k) * log(k) / k^2, where d(k) is the number of divisors of k (A000005).
%H A398008 Matthew Perkins and Robert A. Van Gorder, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11139-018-0037-4">Closed-form calculation of infinite products of Glaisher-type related to Dirichlet series</a>, The Ramanujan Journal, Vol. 49, No. 2 (2019), pp. 371-389. See p. 376, Corollary 2.2.
%F A398008 Equals (Pi^4/18) * (12*log(A) - log(2*Pi) - gamma), where A is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant (A074962) and gamma is Euler's constant (A001620).
%F A398008 In general, for m >= 2, Sum_{k>=1} d_m(k) * log(k) / k^2 = m * zeta(2)^m * (12*log(A) - log(2*Pi) - gamma), where d_m(k) is the m-th Piltz function (see A077592).
%e A398008 3.084410125676432257555879080762184422051016614868918...
%t A398008 RealDigits[(Pi^4/18) * (12*Log[Glaisher] - Log[2*Pi] - EulerGamma), 10, 120][[1]]
%o A398008 (PARI) (Pi^4/18) * (1 - 12*zeta'(-1) - log(2*Pi) - Euler)
%Y A398008 Cf. A000005, A001620, A061444, A073002 (Sum_{k>=1} log(k)/k^2), A074962, A077592, A098198 (Sum_{k>=1} d(k)/k^2), A398009, A398010.
